        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## pKa Values for Oxalic Acid (SRD-46)\n\nOxalic acid (ethanedioic acid, H₂C₂O₄) is a **diprotic acid** with **two dissociation steps**:\n\n| Step | Equilibrium | pKa | T (°C) | I (mol/L) |\n|------|-------------|-----|---------|-----------|\n| 1 | H₂C₂O₄ ⇌ HC₂O₄⁻ + H⁺ | **−1.2** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 2 | HC₂O₄⁻ ⇌ C₂O₄²⁻ + H⁺ | **3.8** | 25 | 0.1 |\n\n*(Source: NIST SRD-46, ligand_8872)*",
